OL,4,Csuspended prison sentence
OL,6,FSentencing Thorpe to a suspended jail
OL,7,Fterm, Judge Rippon said: "That you
OL,8,Fwere able to access police computers
OL,9,Fbecause you were a police officer is
OL,10,Fan additional and very serious
OL,11,Ffeature, but you were ill, you were
OL,12,Flost, and you were acting entirely out
OL,13,Fof character, undoubtedly as you saw
OL,14,Fyour last chance of a family
OL,15,Fdissipate."
OL,17,FThe court heard Thorpe had resigned
OL,18,Ffrom the police, but would probably
OL,19,Fhave been sacked following misconduct
OL,20,Fproceedings after her conviction.
